UML:TaggedValue.value: The numeric value determined by measuring an object.

The type of unit of measure. Note that currently the code for PCE is now C62 and the code for kilometers is KTM. 1. Use the Common Codes of the UNECE Rec 20 2. It is recommended that the measure unit code is provided in this SC rather than in a separately defined BBIE.
The version of the measure unit code list.

An agency that maintains one or more lists of codes. Indicates the agency by means of a code from the latest version of the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list. 1. Use UN EDIFACT 3055 code list. 2. It is recommended that the code list agency is defined either by this identifier or by the code list agency name supplementary component but not both.
The name of the agency that maintains the list of codes. If the agency cannot be identified by any code from the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list, then its name should be provided.
The identification of a list of codes. 1. Indicates the list of codes from which the code content is drawn.
The name of a list of codes.
The Uniform Resource identifier that identifies where the code list scheme is located. 1. May be used to identify the location of the schema of the code list if available across the world wide web
The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the code list is located. 1. May be used to identify the location of the code list if available across the world wide web
The version of the list of codes. 1. Identifies the version of the code list.
The textual equivalent of the code content component. 1. It is recommended that the name of a code is provided in this SC rather than in a separately defined BBIE.
A character string (letters, figures or symbols) that for brevity and/or language independence may be used to represent or replace a definitive value or text of an attribute.
The identifier of the language used in the code name. Use ISO 639-98 1. Identifies the language in which the code name is presented.
A character string used to identify and distinguish uniquely, one instance of an object in an identification scheme from all other objects within the same scheme.
The identification of the agency that maintains the identification scheme. Indicates the agency by means of a code from the latest version of the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list.
The name of the agency that maintains the identification scheme. If the agency cannot be identified by any code from the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list, then its name should be provided.

The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the identification scheme data is located. 1. May be used to identify the location of the identification scheme if available across the world wide web

The identification of the identification scheme. 1. Indicates the identification scheme maintained by the agency. 2. It is recommended that this is identified either by this identifier or by the identification schema name supplementary component not both.
The name of the identification scheme.

The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the identification scheme is located. 1. May be used to identify the location of the schema of the identification scheme if available across the world wide web
The version of the identification scheme. 1. Identifies the version of the identification scheme.
A counted number of non-monetary units possibly including fractions.

The unit of the quantity. 1. If used, use the Common Codes of the UNECE Rec 20 2. It is recommended that if a quantity unit code is provided it should be provided in this SC rather than in a separately defined BBIE 3. If no code list is specified it is assumed to be UNECE Rec 20 (Common Codes).

The identification of the agency that maintains the quantity unit code list. Indicates the agency by means of a code from the latest version of the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list. Indicates the code list maintained by the agency which it is recommended is defined either by identifier or name.
The name of the agency which maintains the quantity unit code list. If the agency cannot be identified by any code from the UN EDIFACT 3055 code list, then its name should be provided.
The value of the indicator. 1. The enumeration is defined by the indicator format text SC.

Whether the indicator is numeric, textual or binary. 1. If this SC is not used it is assumed that the format is True,False unless the format is included in the syntax implementation of the Content Component.
A number of monetary units specificed in a currency where the unit of currencyis explicit or implied.
The version of the UN/ECE rec. 9 code list. 1. If not used, latest version is assumed
The currency of the amount. 1. Use 3 alpha codes UNECE Rec 9. 2. It is recommended that the currency code is provided in this SC rather than in a separately defined BBIE.
The character set of the binary object if the mime type is text.
A set of finite-length sequences of binary octets.
Specifies the decoding algorithm of the binary object.
The filename of the binary object.
The format of the binary content.
The mime type of the binary object.
The Uniform Resource Identifier that identifies where the binary object is located.
Whether the number is an integer, decimal, real number or percentage.
Whether the number is an integer, decimal, real number or percentage. 1. Not to be used as facets can be used instead.
The particular point in the progression of time. 1. This is a string formatted to the date format text SC.

The format of the date time content. 1 Use one of the following 8601 format strings: CC CCYY CCYYMM CCYYMMDD CCYYMMDDhhmmssZhhmm CCYYDDWW MM DD WW MMDD hhZhhmm hhmmZhhmm hhmmssZhhmm hhmmss,ss..Zhhmm mm ss mmss 2 If this SC is not used it is assumed that the format is CCYYMMDDhhmmZhhmm unless the format is included in the syntax implementation of the Date Content Component.
A character string (I.e. a finite set of characters) generally in the form of words of a language.
The identifier of the language used in the content component. 1. Identifies the language in which the code name is presented.
The identification of the locale of the language. 1. Not recommended for use.
